"<div>\n  <h1>Creamy Hamburger Grilled Cheese</h1>\n  <h3>Ingredients:</h3>\n  <ul>\n    <li>4 tablespoons butter, divided</li>\n    <li>1/2 lb. ground hamburger</li>\n    <li>Salt and pepper, to taste</li>\n    <li>8 slices white bread</li>\n    <li>8 oz. cheddar cheese, shredded</li>\n    <li>1/2 cup heavy cream</li>\n  </ul>\n  <h3>Directions:</h3>\n  <ol>\n    <li>Heat a large skillet over medium-high heat.</li>\n    <li>Melt 2 tablespoons of butter in the skillet.</li>\n    <li>Add the ground hamburger to the skillet and season with salt and pepper. Cook until browned, stirring occasionally, for 7-10 minutes.</li>\n    <li>Remove the hamburger from the skillet and set aside.</li>\n    <li>Spread about 1 tablespoon of butter on each slice of bread.</li>\n    <li>Place 4 slices of bread, buttered side down, in the skillet.</li>\n    <li>Evenly distribute the cheddar cheese on the bread in the skillet, then top with the cooked hamburger.</li>\n    <li>Drizzle the heavy cream over the hamburger, then place the remaining slices of bread on top, buttered side up.</li>\n    <li>Grill the sandwiches until golden brown, about 3-4 minutes on each side.</li>\n    <li>Cut sandwiches in half and serve hot.</li>\n  </ol>\n</div>"